    <node id="Based on the story provided, Lexington is angry and frustrated with the expensive, impractical coffee cups because they are a symbol of the larger issue he has with specialization. The cups are fragile, only hold half a cup, require matching saucers, and lose their gold leaf over time. They are not fit for purpose and serve as an example of how specialization can lead to inefficiencies and impractical solutions.&#10;&#10;Lexington believes that the factory could have implemented such advances years ago if they had been willing to abandon their &quot;idiotic notions about specialization.&quot; This is why he is angry and frustrated with the cups, as they represent a larger issue that he sees as holding back progress in the factory." />
