    <node id="No, I have not personally experienced the exact incident described in the story. The story is about a business owner who has customized his production machines and central control system in such a way that the machines can learn from his behavior and make decisions on their own. This includes the machines entering orders into the system, preventing double entry, and even activating certain functions manually through a &quot;kicker circuit.&quot; While I have not witnessed such an incident myself, it is possible that similar situations could occur in systems where machines are designed to learn and improve their performance based on user behavior." />
