    <node id="1. Peter Manners' experience involves going through a series of doors that keep opening on their own, leading him to his job interview with Mr. Lexington at Lex Industries. The soft voice guides him through this process, telling him that Mr. Lexington is expecting him.&#10;2. Peter feels disoriented and anxious due to the unusual situation and being running late for the interview. When he finally reaches Mr. Lexington's office, he finds it more luxurious than he expected, making him feel like he is in Hollywood rather than a factory.&#10;3. During the interview, Mr. Lexington challenges Peter's qualifications and reveals that the factory produces medical equipment and supplies using highly automated systems with robotic arms and machines. This information further unnerves Peter, who has limited practical experience in this field.&#10;4. Despite feeling unnerved and challenged by Mr. Lexington, Peter manages to regain his composure before entering the interview by taking deep breaths, straightening his jacket and tie, and reminding himself that he is qualified for the job. He demonstrates resilience and self-control by letting Mr. Lexington's insulting bellowing roll off his shoulders." />
